title: Hal Tsuchida - Swingin' with the Hammond Organ
description:
Hal Tsuchida - Swingin' with the Hammond Organ

Here you will find jazz organist Hal Tsuchida in a great swinging set with his european friends.


Tracklisting:
01. I'll Drink to That (7:33)
02. Off the Top (6:46)
03. These Foolish Things (8:33)
04. Midnight Creeper (7:12)
05. Tyrone (5:48)
06. That's When We Thought of Love (5:32)
07. How High the Moon (4:22)
08. Our Miss Brooks (9:32)
09. What's Going On (6:56)
10. More Today Than Yesterday (8:02)

Total Time: 70:16


Personnel:
- Hal Tsuchida, Hammond organ
- Torsten Goods, guitar (tracks 1, 2, 4, 6, 8 and 10)
- Tobias Backhaus, drums (tracks 1, 2, 4, 6, 8, and 10)
- Karel Ruzicka Jr., sax (tracks 1, 2, 6, and 8)
- Libor Smoldas, guitar (tracks 3, 5, 7 and 9)
- Tomas Hobzek, drums (tracks 3, 5, 7 and 9)


Recorded at Trixx Studios (Berlin, Germany) July 23 and August 25, 2014
Recording Engineer - Fabio Buemi
Mixing and Mastering - Klaus Scheuermann (4ohm music, Berlin, Germany)
Produced by Harunobu "Hal" Tsuchida

Release: April 3, 2015
Label: Mons Records


Format: MP3 320 kbit/s. All songs are tagged by the book.
